        <p class="metadata">Posted by Thomas Weidner (thomas) on 2008-07-03T10:41:05.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>This is not a bug.</p>

<p>As stated within the API the generic set method returns string/integer.
When you want to have a object returned you must use the specialized setter functions.</p>

<p>This is because Zend_Date provides both ways. When setting a date sometimes it is automatically corrected.</p>

<p>The only way to see if this has happened without parsing the object again is to get the real result as string.</p>

<p>So:
If you need object... use the functions which return object...
If you need string... use the functions which return string...</p>

